Class Transform

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.optimizer.Transform
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AnnotateWithOpTraits, AnnotateWithStatistics, BucketingSortingReduceSinkOptimizer, BucketMapJoinOptimizer, ColumnPruner, ConstantPropagate, CorrelationOptimizer, CountDistinctRewriteProc, FixedBucketPruningOptimizer, Generator, GlobalLimitOptimizer, GroupByOptimizer, HiveOpConverterPostProc, IdentityProjectRemover, JoinReorder, LimitPushdownOptimizer, ListBucketingPruner, MapJoinProcessor, NonBlockingOpDeDupProc, PartitionColumnsSeparator, PartitionConditionRemover, PartitionPruner, PointLookupOptimizer, PredicatePushDown, PredicateTransitivePropagate, ReduceSinkDeDuplication, ReduceSinkJoinDeDuplication, RedundantDynamicPruningConditionsRemoval, SamplePruner, SharedWorkOptimizer, SimpleFetchAggregation, SimpleFetchOptimizer, SimplePredicatePushDown, SkewJoinOptimizer, SortedDynPartitionOptimizer, SortedDynPartitionTimeGranularityOptimizer, SortedMergeBucketMapJoinOptimizer, StatsOptimizer, SyntheticJoinPredicate, UnionProcessor

    public abstract class Transform
extends Object
    Optimizer interface. All the rule-based optimizations implement this interface. All the transformations are invoked sequentially. They take the current parse context (which contains the operator tree among other things), perform all the optimizations, and then return the updated parse context.
